    <div id="PJA10d188" class="doc letter">

     <h2>From Franois Barb-Marbois</h2>
     
     <div class="docbody" xml:lang="fra">
      <div class="opener">
       <div class="openerSeg">3e.</div>
       <table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		  <td class="salutationLeft">Monsieur</td>
		  <td class="salutationRight">A Philadelphie le 18. 8bre. 1780</td>
		</tr>
      </table>
      </div>
      <p>Je viens de recevoir la Lettre que vous maves fait lhonneur de mcrire le 1. du mois de mars dernier. Jai appris dans le tems avec le plus grand plaisir la resolution que vous avies prise demener Mrs. vos fils avec vous. En suivant lexemple<a class="ptr" href="#PJA10d189n1" id="PJA10d189n1-ptr">1</a> de leur pere ils ne peuvent manquer de contracter une sincere amiti pour notre nation. Je vous prie de me rappeller au souvenir de notre petit Compagnon de voyage:<a class="ptr" href="#PJA10d189n2" id="PJA10d189n2-ptr">2</a> et de lassurer du plaisir que jaurai a le revoir soit dans mon pays soit dans le sien.</p>
      <p>Jai des occasions frquentes de mentretenir de vous Mr. avec les amis que vous avs ici. Ils sont en Grand nombre, et les nouvelles quils reoivent de tems en tems de vous me paroissent leur faire le plus Grand plaisir.</p>
      <p>Mr. Le Chev. de la Luzerne est actuellement  Rhode island ou peut tre en chemin pour revenir  Philadelphie. Toute la famille vous prsente ses Compliments; elle a resist asss heureusement  une pidemie<a class="ptr" href="#PJA10d189n3" id="PJA10d189n3-ptr">3</a> qui a dsole Philadelphie cet automne. Je nen ai pas t entirement xempt; mais Jespere men tirer sans accident.</p>
      <p>On nous mande que M. Laurens est prisonnier et quil a t conduit en Angleterre. Si la nouvelle est fonde vous la Saurs probablement plutt que nous.</p>
      <p>Jai Lhonneur dtre avec un respectueux attachement Monsieur Votre trs humble et trs obeissant serviteur,</p>
      <div class="closer">
       <p class="signed">De Marbois</p>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <div id="PJA10d189" class="trans letter">

   
     <h2>Franois Barb-Marbois to John Adams: A Translation</h2>
     
     <div class="docbody">
      <div class="opener">
       <div class="openerSeg">Triplicate</div>
       <table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		  <td class="salutationLeft">Sir</td>
		  <td class="salutationRight">Philadelphia, 18 October 1780</td>
		</tr>
      </table>
      </div>
      <p>I have received the letter that you did me the honor of writing on 1 March. Since then, I have learned with the greatest pleasure of your decision to take your sons with you. By following the example<a class="ptr" href="#PJA10d189n1" id="PJA10d189n1-ptr">1</a> of their father they cannot fail to develop a sincere friendship with our nation. Please remind <span class="pb" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-10-02-pb-0281">[281<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-10/ADMS-06-10-02-pb-0281.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>your little travelling companion<a class="ptr" href="#PJA10d189n2" id="PJA10d189n2-ptr">2</a> of me, and assure him of the pleasure I will have in seeing him again, whether in my country or his.</p>
      <p>I have had many occasions to talk about you to your friends here. They are many, and the news they occasionally receive from you seems to please them greatly.</p>
      <p>The Chevalier de la Luzerne is presently in Rhode Island or perhaps on the road, returning to Philadelphia. The whole family sends its greetings. We fortunately have withstood an epidemic which has afflicted Philadelphia this fall.<a class="ptr" href="#PJA10d189n3" id="PJA10d189n3-ptr">3</a> I was not completely spared, but I hope to escape without further damage.</p>
      <p>We are informed that Mr. Laurens was made prisoner and sent to England. If this news is accurate you will probably know of it before we do.</p>
      <p>I have the honor to be, with respectful devotion, sir, your very humble and very obedient servant,</p>
      <div class="closer">
       <p class="signed">De Marbois</p>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="docback">
      <div class="note-source" id="PJA10d189sn1">
       
   <p>
        <span class="docSource"><span class="dType"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr></span> (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>); marked: 3e.; endorsed: Mr Marbois; docketed by <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Charles Francis Adams (18071886), son of John Quincy Adams and Louisa Catherine Adams ]">CFA</abbr>: October 18. 1780. <span class="dType"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ duplicate ]">Dupl</abbr></span> (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>); marked: 2e; no notations.</span>
       </p>

      </div>
      <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA10d189n1-ptr" id="PJA10d189n1">1</a>
       
   <p>In the duplicate this was followed by the words et les principes.</p>

      </div>
      <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA10d189n2-ptr" id="PJA10d189n2">2</a>
       
   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Quincy Adams (17671848), son of John and Abigail Adams ]">JQA</abbr> and <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> returned to the United States in 1779 aboard <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">La Sensible</span>, on which Barb-Marbois and La Luzerne were fellow passengers.</p>

      </div>
      <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA10d189n3-ptr" id="PJA10d189n3">3</a>
       
   <p>Probably dysentery; see <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Paul H. Smith and others, eds., &lt;i&gt;Letters of Delegates to Congress, 17741789&lt;/i&gt;, Washington, 1976. ]">Smith, ed., <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Letters of Delegates</span></span>, 16:94, 96, 133.</p>

      </div>
